title: UX Lead
---
active: True
---
summary:

We are seeking a UX Lead to manage and grow our design team while shaping the
user experience of our products, such as Tor Browser, Mullvad Browser, Tor VPN
and Tails OS. This role is responsible for leading a team of designers, ensuring
user experiences are intuitive, accessible, and aligned with both user needs and
organizational priorities while helping build a strong, collaborative, and
high-performing design culture.

---
description:

## Overview of the role

TPI is a nonprofit where we are building technology for privacy. This role will
lead product design, working across teams including engineering, product,
communications, and leadership to help create thoughtful, human-centered digital
experiences. The UX Lead will manage and develop a team of researchers and
designers, ensuring the user perspective is embedded throughout the product
development process, from early discovery and research through delivery and
iteration.

This role combines people management with strategic leadership of UX, and
hands-on design work. The UX Lead will set team priorities and workload, support
the growth of individual designers, establish clear UX standards, improve
consistency across products, strengthen collaboration between technical and
non-technical teams, and advocate for accessible, inclusive, and
privacy-conscious design practices. Success in this role requires strong
leadership and people management skills alongside systems thinking, user
empathy, collaboration skills, and the ability to translate complex technical
concepts into clear and effective experiences.

## What you'll do

- Manage a team of designers, and lead end-to-end UX strategy and execution across web and software products
- Set team goals, prioritize work across products and allocate design resources
- Provide regular 1:1s, mentorship, feedback and coaching to support the team’s growth
- Build and sustain a healthy team culture, grounded in openness, collaboration and learning
- Partner closely with Product, Engineering, and Communications teams to shape product direction early
- Support the team as-needed, including with quantitative and qualitative research, journey mapping, wireframing, prototyping and high fidelity design.
- Champion accessibility, inclusive design, and privacy-conscious product experiences
- Establish and evolve design systems, UX standards, and documentation practices
- Mentor and support designers through feedback, coaching, and collaborative critique
- Advocate for user needs while balancing technical constraints, business priorities, and organizational goals
- Use qualitative and quantitative insights to inform design decisions and measure impact
- Help cultivate a healthy design culture grounded in openness, collaboration, and continuous learning

## What We’re Looking For

- Experience managing or formally leading a team of designers, including direct people management responsibilities
- 7+ years of experience in UX, product design, interaction design, or related fields
- Experience leading UX initiatives across complex digital products or platforms
- Must have experience contributing to or maintaining design systems is highly valued
- Familiarity with frontend technologies and constraints e.g. Android/Material Design 3 (must have), Firefox (nice to have), and static websites that function without JavaScript
- Strong portfolio of skills demonstrating systems thinking, interaction design, and user-centered problem solving
- Deep understanding of usability principles, accessibility standards, and responsive design
- Experience conducting or partnering closely on user research
- Comfort working in cross-functional, distributed teams, including leading team members remotely
- Strong communication, facilitation and leadership skills with the ability to align diverse stakeholders and support a team through ambiguity and change
- Proficiency with modern design and prototyping tools specifically Figma

## Nice to Have

- Experience working on open-source products or developer-focused platforms
- Background in privacy, security, accessibility, civic tech, or public-interest technology
- Experience designing for global audiences and multilingual products
- Familiarity with participatory design or community-driven product development

## Compensation

This is a full-time, remote position with flexible geographic location. The
salary range for this position is $110,000 - $121,275 USD. If provided an offer,
TPI will determine the specific compensation package based on skills and years
of experience. TPI provides an attractive benefits package that currently
includes flexible Fridays, unlimited responsible personal time off (RPTO),
generous leave options, healthcare (type is dependent on geographic location),
and a monthly phone and internet stipend, and a tech stipend.

TPI has a strong culture of transparency and democratic processes, and
long-standing community guidelines and cultural norms. At TPI, we are invested
in discussing the depth and breadth of each candidate’s background and
experience during the interview process and using that information to determine
the best offer while considering internal pay equity.

TPI is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate against any
applicant or employee because of race, color, religion, sex, national origin,
disability, genetic information, age, or military or veteran status in
accordance with federal law. Applicants must be authorized to work in the
country in which they live, we cannot provide visa assistance for this position.
Due to U.S. [sanctions and embargo regulations](https://ofac.treasury.gov/sanctions-programs-and-country-information),
TPI is not able to hire individuals with citizenship *and* residency in certain
countries, including but not limited to Russia, North Korea, Cuba, Iraq, China,
Iran, and Syria.

## How to apply

To apply please use this [link](https://www.idealist.org/en/nonprofit-job/b1f838fb80c646cba2ed3f65c930fdc6-ux-team-lead-the-tor-project-winchester) which will take you to a brief application. You
will be asked to answer a few initial questions and **upload your CV or resume**,
and your portfolio. We do not ask for references or cover letters at this time.
Please do not include them. Additionally, please do not use AI for the creation
of your application or at any point in the process. Applications will be
considered on a rolling basis and we reserve the right to close this process
early due to high applicant volume.

**Deadline: July 8, 2026 by 21:00 UTC**
